Mission
-------

Cave Runtime is AGPL-3.0-or-later by deliberate choice. The intent is
to keep the platform open and serving humanity:

  * Hyperscalers (Amazon Web Services, Google Cloud, Microsoft Azure)
    and other large SaaS vendors cannot take Cave Runtime, modify it
    behind closed doors, and re-sell the result as a closed managed
    service. AGPL §13 ("Remote Network Interaction") requires that
    anyone who runs a modified Cave Runtime as a network service make
    the corresponding source available to every user of that service.
  * Operators who self-host Cave Runtime — including commercial
    operators serving paying customers — keep all the freedoms the
    license grants, with the single obligation that modifications
    surface to their users on the same terms.
  * Sovereign-by-default: the platform must remain operable without
    any external SaaS in the critical path, by anyone, anywhere.

This is "insanlığa hizmet" — service to humanity, in Turkish.

Upstream attribution
--------------------

Cave Runtime re-implements the wire protocols, behaviors, and APIs of
the upstream projects listed below in pure Rust (line-by-line TDD
parity, per ADR-GOLDEN-001 / docs/adr/internal/ADR-GOLDEN-*). Cave
Runtime does NOT vendor or redistribute upstream source code; each
upstream is independently licensed by its own authors.

License strings below are extracted from each crate's
`parity.manifest.toml`. Verify against the upstream's authoritative
LICENSE file before redistribution of any derived artifact. The
canonical machine-readable list lives in
`crates/cave-upstream/src/projects.rs` and is exposed at runtime via
`/api/portal/upstream`.

